# Dedovo, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Dedovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Dedovsky Selsoviet, Fyodorovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 328 as of 2010. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Dedovo is located 16&nbsp;km southwest of Fyodorovka (the district's administrative centre) by road. Novaya Derevnya is the nearest rural locality.
